            <p>University degree doesnâ€™t make you a professional however thanks to my management studies I was more or less ready to take on the challenge.</p>
            <p>Over the last couple of years I have been an <strong>Engineering Manager</strong> and <strong>managed big sized teaching teams</strong> that were working for coding bootcamps. Big sized meaning around 30 people on irregular schedule with varying experience ranging from junior assistants to experts with years of experience.</p>
